# patches/build/windows/series — Windows-only build-fix patches, applied by
# build/build-windows.ps1 (via GNU patch) AFTER the main patches/series, ONLY on
# the Windows builder. They must NOT go in the main patches/series: they touch
# targets (the //chrome/installer/setup + //rlz graph) that only Windows evaluates,
# and mac/Linux builds are already green without them. Paths RELATIVE TO patches/.
# Blank + '#' lines ignored. Same GNU-patch apply path as the raven series, so CRLF
# checkouts are fine.

# ============================ ACTIVE ============================
# ungoogled forces enable_rlz_support=false everywhere, but the Windows installer
# (//chrome/installer/setup, //rlz:rlz_id) references the rlz library unconditionally,
# so `gn gen` fails "Unresolved dependencies". Restore the upstream value; RLZ pings
# stay off via enable_rlz (raven isn't Chrome-branded). See the patch header for why
# this adds no rlz code to chrome.exe.
build/windows/raven-rlz-restore-support.patch
